"{\"uid\": \"independent.co.uk-news-uk-home-news-princess-anne-paris-royal-family-olympics-b2585206.html\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Notifications can be managed in browser preferences.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 52, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Please refresh the page or navigate to another page on the site to be automatically logged inPlease refresh your browser to be logged in  Swipe for next article  Anne has slowly been returning to royal duties after she was rushed to hospital following a horse accident in June  Removed from bookmarks  I would like to be emailed about offers, events and updates from The Independent.\", \"from\": 54, \"to\": 437, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Read ourPrivacy notice  Princess Annehas been pictured inParisalongside other royals in her first international appearance since she waskicked in the head by a horse.\", \"from\": 438, \"to\": 604, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"ThePrincess Royal, who serves on theInternational Olympic Committee(IOC), was seen withPrince Albertof Monaco and others ahead of the games on 26 July.\", \"from\": 606, \"to\": 757, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 674, \"end\": 677, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 0.9999999999995453, \"rank\": 3.3384521105984296e-13, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 709, \"end\": 715, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Monaco\", \"score\": 0.9999554839884875, \"rank\": 4.352354830273071e-05, \"text\": \"Monaco\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Monaco\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Monaco\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The 73-year-old has slowly beenreturning to royal dutiesafter she wasrushed to hospitalon 23 June with concussion after a \\\"horse-related\\\" incident on her Gatcombe Park estate in Gloucestershire.\", \"from\": 759, \"to\": 953, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 937, \"end\": 952, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gloucestershire\", \"score\": 0.99999989639287, \"rank\": 1.0352271086311412e-07, \"text\": \"Gloucestershire\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gloucestershire\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gloucestershire\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Anne's medical team said her head injuries were consistent with a potential impact from a horse's head or legs, but her concussion has meant precise details of how the incident came about are not clear.\", \"from\": 955, \"to\": 1157, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It was understood the princess was walking within the protected perimeter of the 730-acre estate when the incident occurred last month.\", \"from\": 1159, \"to\": 1294, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"She was riding beside Prince William and Prince Edward at the time, and Edward can be seen in footage turning around after realising there was a problem with her horse, Noble.\", \"from\": 1296, \"to\": 1471, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1318, \"end\": 1332, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_IV\", \"score\": 0.9998985865067462, \"rank\": 9.714288698194883e-05, \"text\": \"Prince William\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_IV\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_IV\"}, {\"begin\": 1337, \"end\": 1343, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Prince_Michael_of_Kent\", \"score\": 0.9841100379338377, \"rank\": 0.012639884579654558, \"text\": \"Prince\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Prince_Michael_of_Kent\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Prince_Michael_of_Kent\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As an experienced horsewoman, it was widely reported that the princess's recent injuries would not deter her from interacting with the animals.\", \"from\": 1473, \"to\": 1616, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"However, she did miss several engagements after the accident, including the state banquet for a Japanese state visit and a trip to Canada.\", \"from\": 1618, \"to\": 1756, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1714, \"end\": 1722, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japanese_language\", \"score\": 0.9815404667443656, \"rank\": 0.01875121249645897, \"text\": \"Japanese\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japanese_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japanese_language\"}, {\"begin\": 1749, \"end\": 1755, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada\", \"score\": 0.9196474244495476, \"rank\": 0.08682325754223037, \"text\": \"Canada\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It was not her first horse-related injury and she previously suffered concussion while riding in the 1976 Olympic Games.\", \"from\": 1758, \"to\": 1878, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"She became a member of the IOC in 1988.\", \"from\": 1879, \"to\": 1918, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1906, \"end\": 1909, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 0.9999999999995453, \"rank\": 3.3384521105984296e-13, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Her daughter, Zara Tindall, who won a team silver medal for Great Britain at the London 2012 Olympics, said the princess remained a keen equestrian decades after her showjumping heyday in the Seventies.\", \"from\": 1920, \"to\": 2122, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1934, \"end\": 1946, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zara_Tindall\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Zara Tindall\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zara_Tindall\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zara_Tindall\"}, {\"begin\": 1980, \"end\": 1993, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"score\": 0.45822520285946067, \"rank\": 0.8089965820940762, \"text\": \"Great Britain\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\"}, {\"begin\": 2001, \"end\": 2021, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999999999843112, \"rank\": 1.5778744655223626e-11, \"text\": \"London 2012 Olympics\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Our horses are in our family, so there is always discussions about performances and things like that,\\\" she toldPeoplelast year.\", \"from\": 2124, \"to\": 2252, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"There is horses in her life, and she does a bit of breeding as well.\", \"from\": 2254, \"to\": 2323, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"So there is always horse conversation going on,\\\" Mrs Tindall added.\", \"from\": 2324, \"to\": 2391, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Join thought-provoking conversations, follow other Independent readers and see their replies  Please refresh the page or navigate to another page on the site to be automatically logged inPlease refresh your browser to be logged in\", \"from\": 2393, \"to\": 2623, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2444, \"end\": 2455, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Independent\", \"score\": 0.9999999904953256, \"rank\": 4.972104964145411e-09, \"text\": \"Independent\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q11032\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Independent\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/r